8.2 Pythagorean Theorem and Pythagorean

Triples

Here you'll learn how to use the Pythagorean Theorem, which states that given a right triangle with legs of lengths

a and b and a hypotenuse of length c, a2 +b2 = c2. You'll also learn the theorem's converse and what a Pythagorean

Triple is.

What if you were told that a triangle had side lengths of 5, 12, and 13? How could you determine if the triangle were

a right one? After completing this Concept, you'll be able to use the Pythagorean Theorem to solve problems like

this one.

